TextBody:
Hello Alex,

Thank you for meeting with me today. In our session we modified your existing permissions report to filter for only Domain Groups, excluding service principles and Domain Users. We re-ran the report, and it seems to correctly show only Group permissions.

Unfortunately, I was unable to help change the folder paths to the associated Share paths (e.g.: E:filessharename to \Serversharename). This is probably possible, but the table the report is using doesn't include that information, so you would have to join multiple tables together. Like we discussed, I'm limited in how much I can help with this type of custom report creation.

Feel free to continue to play around with the SQL View Creation Analysis task. Let me know if you're able to make any progress, or if you'd like to schedule another meeting to work on that some more.

Thank you,

Joshua Sexton
Technical Support Engineer Tier 1
